role-oriented desktop application designed for office environments where
multiple Windows systems are connected via LAN. It allows admins and users to manage
attendance, leave, projects, work reports, and billing efficiently. The system operates on a
client-server model with the server hosting the central database and connected client
systems.
2. User Roles and Dashboards
**Admin:** Full control over users, projects, reports, and billing. Can add/edit/delete data
and view reports.
**User:** Can log attendance, apply leave, submit work reports, and view their performance
and earnings.
3. Core Modules and Features
3.1 Attendance Management
- Admin can view, edit, and delete attendance records.
- Users can clock in and clock out daily.
- Attendance data should be downloadable (PDF/CSV).
- Daily, weekly, and monthly summaries.
3.2 Leave Management
- Users can apply for leave.
- Admin can approve or reject leave requests.
- Leave data is stored for reporting.
3.3 User Management
- Admin can add, edit, or delete users.
- Admin sets username and password for each user.
- Users can update their profiles (profile picture, contact info).
- Admin can reset passwords; users can change their own.

3.4 Project Management
- Admin can create, edit, delete, and hold projects (individually or in bulk).
- Each project includes: Project Name, Object ID, Pages, Characters, Records, and Formula
for billing.
- Example Formulas:
- Formula 1: (pages × 0.05) + ((characters / 1000) × 4.75)
- Formula 2: (records × 0.25)
- Admin can define billing formulas per project.
3.5 Work Reports
- Users can submit daily/weekly/monthly work reports.
- Reports link to project fields (Object ID, pages, etc.).
- Duplicate Object ID check before overwrite.
- Billing formula triggers after submission.
- System shows total objects and earnings per day.
- Reports are filterable by date, user, and project.
3.6 Billing Management
- Calculates total earnings per project and user.
- Displays detailed breakdown of earnings.
- Admin can view all user billing reports.
- Users can view their own earnings.
4. Reports and Exports
- All reports (attendance, leaves, work, billing) are downloadable.
- Filterable by date, user, and project.
- Admin dashboard includes daily, weekly, and monthly summaries.
5. Authentication and Security
- Role-based login system (Admin/User).
- Password encryption and secure storage.
- Password reset and change options.
- Session-based authentication for LAN users.
